15/12/2002
ATHENS, Greece -- Mayor-elect Dora Bakoyianni narrowly escaped an assassination attempt on Friday (13 December), outside her political office in the centre of Athens.A man fired a shotgun at her car, seriously wounding her driver.
Bakoyianni suffered minor injuries to her face and hands from flying window glass.
Later the police detained the alleged assailant, 35-year-old Giorgos Sandalis, who is described as a former mental patient.
On Saturday he was charged with attempted murder and illegal arms possession.
When she takes office in January, Bakoyianni will become Athens' first female mayor.
(ANA, Kathimerini - 14/12/02)
